cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.COM, cs.NI, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with deriving an improved sphere-packing bound for communication channels. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the tightness of the bound through computer simulations of iteratively decoded turbo-like codes. 
3. cs.COM (Computer Networks and Communications) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with improving the performance of communication systems through better coding techniques. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with improving the performance of communication channels, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper deals with improving the performance of communication systems, which can be relevant to social networks.
